## Navigation Levels

This template supports navigation levels where:

1. **Header** shows root-level pages as tabs (when `site_navigation: true`)
2. **LeftPanel** shows pages under the current root section

This creates a GitBook-like experience.

## Components

| Component | Description | Key Parameters |
|-----------|-------------|----------------|
| **Header** | Navigation header with tabs | `sticky`, `site_navigation` |
| **LeftPanel** | Sidebar navigation | `collapsible`, `site_navigation` |
| **DocSection** | Main content renderer | `show_navigation`, `max_width` |
| **Footer** | Simple site footer | - |

## Content Authoring

Documentation pages use markdown with YAML frontmatter:

```markdown
---
type: DocSection
---

### Category Name

# Page Title

## Subtitle

Content goes here...
```

### Adding a New Page

1. Create folder: `site/pages/guide/my-topic/`
2. Add `page.yml`:
   ```yaml
   title: My Topic
   order: 3
   ```
3. Add `1-content.md` with your documentation

## Building

```bash
# Build foundation
cd foundation && pnpm build

# Build site for production
cd site && pnpm build
```

Deploy `site/dist/` to any static host.

